1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,400
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,400 --> 00:00:02,800
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,600 --> 00:00:05,800
(Episode 17)

4
00:00:07,400 --> 00:00:09,200
Let's go for a third round.

5
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:14,300
Koreans always do three rounds, you know.

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,400
She looks pretty drunk,

7
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,700
so let's get Ms. Cho Eun Ae
in a cab first.

8
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:19,200
Yeah, that sounds good.

9
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:23,133
I know where she lives, so I'll take her.

10
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:29,200
I'll take care of my team member.

11
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:32,333
Sorry? Okay.

12
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,133
Get in.

13
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:38,323
What? We need to go for a third round!

14
00:00:38,323 --> 00:00:39,600
There's no third round. Just get in.

15
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,864
Let's go for a third round!

16
00:00:41,900 --> 00:00:43,037
Good night, Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

17
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:45,500
Good work.

18
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,400
The team manager's nicer than he lets on.

19
00:00:48,833 --> 00:00:50,800
I thought he didn't care
about the team at all.

20
00:00:50,933 --> 00:00:51,933
This is unexpected.

21
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,300
"I'll take care of my team member."

22
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:57,683
Isn't that a bit much?

23
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,900
Since when did he care that much?

24
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,500
I called a driver. You can ride with me.

25
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,900
- I'll drop you off.
- No.

26
00:01:10,579 --> 00:01:13,300
I left something at the office,
so I need to stop by.

27
00:01:13,933 --> 00:01:15,100
Get home safely, everyone.

28
00:01:16,433 --> 00:01:17,600
- Get home safely.
- You too.

29
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:18,800
Have a safe trip, Manager.

30
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:23,600
I'll head home as well.

31
00:01:23,600 --> 00:01:25,833
If anyone's going for a third round,

32
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:28,300
use this.

33
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:32,435
Is this the famous black card?

34
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:36,500
Don't drink so much
that it affects tomorrow's meeting. Bye.

35
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:38,200
Thank you.

36
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:42,600
Get out. Hurry.

37
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,633
Is this the right neighborhood?

38
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:48,808
Yes, warm-hearted people and clean water,

39
00:01:48,808 --> 00:01:51,033
Jeongdam-dong. This is my neighborhood.

40
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,312
Then take care.

41
00:01:54,312 --> 00:01:55,312
Go on in.

42
00:01:57,933 --> 00:01:58,933
Careful.

43
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:02,125
Watch it.

44
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,616
- What the?
- Come here.

45
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:09,233
What is this?

46
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:11,800
What's this?

47
00:02:15,733 --> 00:02:17,568
Where's your house?

48
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,419
My house? This way.

49
00:02:23,072 --> 00:02:25,300
That way. No.

50
00:02:26,033 --> 00:02:27,300
It should be around here.

51
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:29,819
Are you sure this is the right place?
Did you get off at the wrong place?

52
00:02:29,819 --> 00:02:30,888
Look at me!

53
00:02:30,888 --> 00:02:33,061
Hey, what do you take me for?

54
00:02:33,633 --> 00:02:35,500
I may be just an intern,

55
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:37,100
but you think I can't find my own house?

56
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,600
I'm telling you, it's here.

57
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,500
We're here.

58
00:02:43,733 --> 00:02:46,120
Where is your house?

59
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,700
Who's this?

60
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:53,100
Team Manager, what are you doing here?

61
00:02:54,500 --> 00:02:55,500
What?

62
00:02:56,465 --> 00:02:57,465
Hey, Cho Eun Ae.

63
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,400
Ham Cho Rong!

64
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:00,833
My pretty friend.

65
00:03:02,133 --> 00:03:03,800
Say hello.

66
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,100
We started on the same team together.

67
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:08,947
Your co-worker? Hello.

68
00:03:08,947 --> 00:03:10,233
I'm Eun Ae's friend, Ham Cho Rong.

69
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:11,800
I'm Ko Gyeol.

70
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,700
Cho Rong, since we met like this,

71
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:17,300
let's have just one more drink
at your restaurant.

72
00:03:17,933 --> 00:03:20,581
No, where is your house?

73
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,243
He's right. You're too drunk. Go inside.

74
00:03:23,243 --> 00:03:24,300
Hey.

75
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:26,500
Three rounds! Go inside.

76
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,900
What? Go where?

77
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:28,900
What do you mean, three rounds?

78
00:03:30,493 --> 00:03:32,900
Makgeolli with bindaetteok,
bindaetteok with makgeolli.

79
00:03:32,900 --> 00:03:33,900
That's the rule.

80
00:03:34,733 --> 00:03:38,533
But hasn't she been
in the bathroom too long?

81
00:03:39,429 --> 00:03:40,529
She'll come out when she's ready.

82
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,933
Since you're her co-worker,

83
00:03:43,200 --> 00:03:44,952
it must be tough for you too.

84
00:03:44,952 --> 00:03:46,152
Yes.

85
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:48,233
Because of that mess of a team manager.

86
00:03:51,533 --> 00:03:53,133
Mess of a... What?

87
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:55,000
He shows up for only ten seconds.

88
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:56,800
He's reckless, rude, slick,
and irresponsible.

89
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,000
She says it's unbearable.

90
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,803
So it must be hard for you too,

91
00:04:00,803 --> 00:04:02,211
working under someone like that.

92
00:04:03,459 --> 00:04:04,500
I see.

93
00:04:12,244 --> 00:04:13,611
What's that on your ears?

94
00:04:14,933 --> 00:04:16,635
My ears suddenly felt cold,

95
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:20,500
and I found these earmuffs in my pocket.

96
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:22,400
They fit perfectly.

97
00:04:25,675 --> 00:04:27,589
This is Cho Rong's bindaetteok.

98
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:29,733
- I washed my hands.
- What?

99
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:31,500
- It's fine...
- Go ahead, try it.

100
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:34,800
How is it, Team Manager?

101
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:37,200
The bindaetteok here is really good,
right?

102
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:39,800
- Yes.
- What? Team Manager?

103
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:41,600
Eun Ae, who is this?

104
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:42,700
My team manager.

105
00:04:43,200 --> 00:04:46,845
Ko Gyeol, the noble one himself.

106
00:04:47,633 --> 00:04:50,200
My goodness, I'm so sorry.

107
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,100
No, you have nothing to apologize for.

108
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:56,100
You just repeated what you heard.

109
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:57,833
Cho Rong,

110
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:01,555
his name is Ko Gyeol,
which sounds like "noble."

111
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,033
Noble, my foot.

112
00:05:03,856 --> 00:05:05,400
Isn't that ironic?

113
00:05:07,133 --> 00:05:08,720
Eun Ae, stop it.

114
00:05:09,300 --> 00:05:11,563
Excuse me, Team Manager Ko Gyeol,

115
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:15,224
if you're noble, I'm a good girl.

116
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:17,800
A very, very good girl.

117
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,300
Good girl.

118
00:05:23,971 --> 00:05:25,100
My stomach.

119
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:27,900
Cho Rong,

120
00:05:27,900 --> 00:05:30,300
hold my stomach. I'm going to burst.

121
00:05:32,221 --> 00:05:33,500
I need to go home and check!

122
00:05:35,973 --> 00:05:37,968
Team Manager, hold my stomach.

123
00:05:37,968 --> 00:05:38,968
What's wrong with you?

124
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,300
My stomach.

125
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:45,200
Eun Ae!

126
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:48,333
She's such a handful.

127
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,288
My back hurts.

128
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,400
Why am I sleeping here?

129
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:11,400
Wait, how did I get home yesterday?

130
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:14,233
I don't remember.

131
00:06:16,233 --> 00:06:18,400
What are these?

132
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,900
If I don't remember anything,

133
00:06:23,300 --> 00:06:25,200
then nothing must have happened.

134
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,400
- Where's Seung Wu?
- I don't know.

135
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:37,433
He hasn't come out of his room
since last night.

136
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,000
I don't know if he's sleeping or crying.

137
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,200
Seung Ri, go to work first.

138
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,733
I'll check on him first.

139
00:06:43,733 --> 00:06:45,481
Okay. I'll see you later.

140
00:06:45,481 --> 00:06:46,481
Bye.

141
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,149
Don't try to comfort him,

142
00:06:50,149 --> 00:06:53,432
saying things like "cheer up"
or "keep trying."

143
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:08,200
Seo Seung Wu.

144
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:11,000
It's just the preliminaries.

145
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:12,800
Don't say anything.

146
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,500
Nothing you say will comfort me.

147
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:20,100
There's something in kendo called zanshin.

148
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:23,433
It means staying alert...

149
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,520
and not letting your guard down,
even after you strike.

150
00:07:27,733 --> 00:07:29,000
From what I've seen in life,

151
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,300
the one who keeps that mindset...

152
00:07:32,533 --> 00:07:35,733
and endures the longest ends up winning.

153
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,433
If it's something you truly love,

154
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:47,933
don't give up. Keep trying.

155
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:51,933
I'll support you
until you achieve your dream.

156
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:53,933
And...

157
00:07:55,033 --> 00:07:57,000
I take pride in what I do.

158
00:07:58,133 --> 00:08:00,000
Your dad's an executive at Kangsu Group.

159
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:03,300
What are you talking about
all of a sudden?

160
00:08:04,013 --> 00:08:06,900
It might have looked to you...

161
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:10,000
like I was groveling and begging,

162
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:12,133
but I'm not ashamed at all.

163
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,400
I really am a secretary by nature.

164
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,933
Did you happen to read my webtoon?

165
00:08:20,233 --> 00:08:22,200
I just saw the title in passing.

166
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:24,400
Dad.

167
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:27,633
Get up, eat, and get back to work.

168
00:08:28,733 --> 00:08:31,171
You said it's a hardcore revenge story
this time.

169
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,200
I'm off.

170
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:44,533
Dad.

171
00:08:48,333 --> 00:08:50,933
(Kangsu Construction)

172
00:08:58,875 --> 00:09:00,776
Right, nothing happened.

173
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,933
I mixed drinks perfectly,

174
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:06,893
and we had a fun,
constructive conversation,

175
00:09:06,893 --> 00:09:07,893
then went to karaoke.

176
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:10,500
We had a great time there...

177
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,500
and then went back home.

178
00:09:12,133 --> 00:09:14,040
What more could there be?

179
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,475
So don't panic, Cho Eun Ae.

180
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,300
Good morning, Team Manager.

181
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,633
Did you get home safely yesterday?

182
00:09:29,664 --> 00:09:31,664
I had so much fun at karaoke...

183
00:09:31,664 --> 00:09:33,500
that I'm a bit sore today.

184
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:37,300
No wonder.
Do you remember going to karaoke?

185
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:40,024
Yes, I was fine up until then.

186
00:09:40,933 --> 00:09:43,000
Up until then? Then after that?

187
00:09:43,365 --> 00:09:44,800
What?

188
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:47,900
Did we go somewhere else?

189
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:52,000
Did you go for a third round without me?

190
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:55,100
No.

191
00:09:55,100 --> 00:09:57,500
You were so drunk. Where else would we go?

192
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:58,987
Right?

193
00:10:00,700 --> 00:10:01,700
Here.

194
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:03,500
What is this?

195
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,755
You drank a lot, so it's a hangover cure.

196
00:10:07,033 --> 00:10:08,179
No, thanks.

197
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,900
Come on, try it.

198
00:10:29,433 --> 00:10:31,011
Good morning, Manager.

199
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,533
Good morning.

200
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,488
- You're early again today.
- Yes.

201
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,700
Yes? Understood.

202
00:10:42,233 --> 00:10:45,000
I'll stop by the CPO's office...

203
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:48,900
and then head out.

204
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,100
Would you like one too, Manager?

205
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:54,900
No, thank you.

206
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,733
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, can we talk for a moment?

207
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:04,700
Sorry? Okay.

208
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,300
Team Manager Ko Gyeol and I...

209
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,800
have known each other for a long time.

210
00:11:12,733 --> 00:11:15,781
So that's why you knew his tastes so well.

211
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:20,032
The reason I'm telling you this is,

212
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,900
while we've been close personally
for over 25 years,

213
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:26,800
we don't show that relationship at work.

214
00:11:27,300 --> 00:11:29,700
Sorry? That means...

215
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,576
That's not it.

216
00:11:32,576 --> 00:11:34,100
I don't have any personal relationship
with him.

217
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,917
Of course I know that,

218
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:38,640
but you tend to be...

219
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,600
a bit too informal with people.

220
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,033
Me?

221
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:43,955
Until now, that attitude...

222
00:11:43,955 --> 00:11:46,000
probably hasn't caused issues,

223
00:11:46,633 --> 00:11:47,633
but it's different here.

224
00:11:48,100 --> 00:11:50,251
Do you remember when you shouted
at him during the protest...

225
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,400
to give your child back?

226
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:55,133
Yes,

227
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,300
I mistook him for the CPO.

228
00:11:57,600 --> 00:12:00,200
That video got uploaded to the intranet.

229
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:03,627
It caused rumors that he abandoned a woman
and took her child,

230
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:05,833
and it put him in a difficult position.

231
00:12:06,168 --> 00:12:07,875
- What?
- We can't have him...

232
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:10,900
be misunderstood like that again, right?

233
00:12:12,928 --> 00:12:14,800
I understand.

234
00:12:15,233 --> 00:12:16,700
I'll be more careful.

235
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,400
You can go now.

236
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,333
Okay then.

237
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:35,700
What's wrong with me?

238
00:12:36,433 --> 00:12:38,219
What is it?
Why are you calling this early?

239
00:12:38,633 --> 00:12:40,000
Where are you? Did you go to work?

240
00:12:40,700 --> 00:12:42,573
Of course I did. Why?

241
00:12:43,833 --> 00:12:44,833
What did your team manager say?

242
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,400
No, I'm sure it was worse than that.

243
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:48,800
Did you get fired?

244
00:12:49,133 --> 00:12:50,700
Fired? Why would I?

245
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:54,400
You really don't remember anything?
Nothing?

246
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:59,000
Was there something...

247
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:00,733
I really needed to remember?

248
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:03,500
You dragged your team manager
to the restaurant last night...

249
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,533
and said, "If you're noble,
then I'm a good girl,"

250
00:13:05,533 --> 00:13:07,187
and told him to hold your stomach
so it wouldn't burst.

251
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:09,184
You were a total mess.

252
00:13:09,675 --> 00:13:11,300
What? Me?

253
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,928
Yes, you.

254
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,200
But...

255
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:18,309
I think I made things worse.

256
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,400
I repeated what you said...

257
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,500
Maybe I exaggerated it a little.

258
00:13:24,900 --> 00:13:27,400
What did you say exactly?

259
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,277
That he's a slick, rude,

260
00:13:30,613 --> 00:13:31,891
reckless team manager, and how hard...

261
00:13:31,891 --> 00:13:33,448
it must be working under him.

262
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:36,947
I had no idea he was your team manager...

263
00:13:36,947 --> 00:13:38,608
because you said he was your co-worker.

264
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:41,833
When did I say that?

265
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:45,032
Well, I might've emphasized it a bit.

266
00:13:46,211 --> 00:13:49,256
Forget it. Just quit already.

267
00:13:49,256 --> 00:13:50,433
At least save face.

268
00:13:51,328 --> 00:13:52,328
What did you say?

269
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:54,669
Hey, I have to go. Emergency!

270
00:13:55,833 --> 00:13:57,709
Grandma! It hurts!

271
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:01,125
I must be crazy.

272
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:02,533
What do I do now?

273
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:10,400
Should I really just quit?
Then what about Joy?

274
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:12,800
Let's avoid him for now.

275
00:14:15,233 --> 00:14:18,700
Eun Ae finally caused trouble.

276
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,093
And you made it worse.

277
00:14:21,533 --> 00:14:24,403
You two should both be buried.

278
00:14:24,403 --> 00:14:26,571
What a mess.

279
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:29,600
Grandma,
why have you been so harsh lately?

280
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,933
Mrs. Park Sun Bun.

281
00:14:31,500 --> 00:14:33,400
Did you take Ms. Cho Eun Ae
home safely yesterday?

282
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:35,400
Yes.

283
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,500
Since when do you care
about your team members?

284
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:41,300
Did you grow fond of your team?

285
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,900
Didn't you call me for something?

286
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:48,300
Drop the formalities.
I have a favor to ask.

287
00:14:49,900 --> 00:14:51,700
Can you actually put in some real effort?

288
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:55,833
Not just pretend,
really compete this time.

289
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,900
I am putting in real effort.

290
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,900
Then why are you neglecting your team
like that?

291
00:15:03,100 --> 00:15:04,900
The first round is in a month.

292
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:09,500
Wait. Are you being so relaxed...

293
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,900
because you think I'm not a match for you?

294
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,200
It's not that.

295
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:15,000
I just haven't figured things out yet.

296
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,000
All right.

297
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:20,133
Figure it out soon,
and let's compete properly.

298
00:15:20,633 --> 00:15:21,633
I'll be expecting it.

299
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,700
You seem different these days.

300
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,433
Different?

301
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:30,821
I'm telling you not to be a deadweight...

302
00:15:30,821 --> 00:15:32,900
living off company money.
Take it to heart.

303
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:36,600
Got it. Thanks for the advice.
I'll get going then.

304
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:46,033
What on earth happened?

305
00:15:46,033 --> 00:15:47,900
Why did you do that? Just why?

306
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:48,933
Seriously.

307
00:15:50,500 --> 00:15:56,600
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>
- <i>Calling "Mom, Mom"</i>

308
00:15:57,000 --> 00:16:01,171
What? Who did I sing this with?

309
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:04,000
This is driving me crazy.

310
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:09,000
What's wrong with her?

311
00:16:12,133 --> 00:16:13,400
Something came back to her.

312
00:16:14,500 --> 00:16:16,813
- Yeah, it must be painful.
- I'm going nuts.

313
00:16:16,813 --> 00:16:18,233
Of course it is.

314
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,900
Fine, just quit.

315
00:16:22,448 --> 00:16:23,595
No, not my Joy.

316
00:16:24,533 --> 00:16:26,900
Do it. No, not my Joy.

317
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:28,600
Fine. No!

318
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,833
Fine. No!

319
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:31,800
Fine. No!

320
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,000
No.

321
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:34,800
Your head's not going to explode
if you do that.

322
00:16:39,900 --> 00:16:41,933
I'll be out on field work today
and heading straight home.

323
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,500
Clock out on your own.

324
00:16:50,984 --> 00:16:51,984
That's a relief.

325
00:16:52,233 --> 00:16:54,469
At least I won't run into him today.

326
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:59,253
Don't worry about the office.
Have a productive day out.

327
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:01,700
Thank you.

328
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,797
Thank you.

329
00:17:04,133 --> 00:17:05,133
Thank you.

330
00:17:08,233 --> 00:17:09,233
Well, well.

331
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:21,700
Bit Na got to kindergarten safely.

332
00:17:24,333 --> 00:17:25,500
What are you doing?

333
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,500
Let's talk.

334
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:29,900
Do we really have to?

335
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,400
We're the kind of couple...

336
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,000
who understands each other without words.

337
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,600
No, I don't know how you feel.

338
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,900
So let's start over.

339
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:50,100
What do you mean you got the position
but won't take it?

340
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:51,866
I told you,

341
00:17:51,866 --> 00:17:54,700
they demanded 200,000 dollars
as a condition.

342
00:17:55,433 --> 00:17:57,033
We don't have that kind of money.

343
00:17:57,300 --> 00:17:59,733
Even if we did, I wouldn't do it.

344
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:02,411
Why not? If we had it,

345
00:18:02,411 --> 00:18:04,700
we should pay whatever it takes.

346
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,133
Honey, I'm a philosopher...

347
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:08,900
who studies human existence and value.

348
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:13,269
How could I abandon
my conscience and pride...

349
00:18:13,933 --> 00:18:16,368
and buy a professorship with money?

350
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:19,300
Why does that matter so much?

351
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:21,381
You should figure out
how to get the money...

352
00:18:21,381 --> 00:18:23,600
and seize the opportunity.

353
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:24,912
How can you say that?

354
00:18:25,733 --> 00:18:27,600
That's something I could never do,

355
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,301
not in the past, present, or future.

356
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:32,633
Shouldn't you at least respect my beliefs?

357
00:18:32,900 --> 00:18:35,195
Aren't you upset...

358
00:18:35,195 --> 00:18:37,100
about all those years of hard studying...

359
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,800
and struggling as a lecturer?

360
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:46,000
More than that,
are you even thinking about Bit Na and me?

361
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:47,833
Thinking of her, I can't do it even more.

362
00:18:48,900 --> 00:18:50,800
I might be an incapable father,

363
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,700
but I won't be a shameful one.

364
00:18:53,133 --> 00:18:54,133
So in the end,

365
00:18:55,700 --> 00:18:56,896
you won't do it?

366
00:19:00,300 --> 00:19:02,033
No, I won't.

367
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:13,900
What are you doing?

368
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,100
Repenting.

369
00:19:16,500 --> 00:19:19,633
Repenting? To whom?
What did you do wrong?

370
00:19:19,700 --> 00:19:22,033
To both you and Dad.

371
00:19:23,291 --> 00:19:25,035
Because you failed the preliminaries?

372
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:27,400
Enough. Come out and eat.

373
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:30,200
What's the point
of someone like me eating?

374
00:19:31,233 --> 00:19:32,333
Blinded by ambition,

375
00:19:32,333 --> 00:19:34,300
I even used my parents as material.

376
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,997
I couldn't even understand...

377
00:19:35,997 --> 00:19:37,656
my father's boundless heart.

378
00:19:39,033 --> 00:19:41,100
I deserve to starve.

379
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:42,300
Starve.

380
00:19:42,433 --> 00:19:43,500
What are you talking about?

381
00:19:44,400 --> 00:19:47,600
Did you use us as material?

382
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:49,400
What is it? Let me see.

383
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,648
It's gone. I deleted everything.

384
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:58,800
Hello?

385
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,233
Yes, this is Seo Seung Wu,

386
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:03,233
the one who submitted
"Secretary by Nature."

387
00:20:03,733 --> 00:20:06,433
What? "Secretary by Nature?" That punk...

388
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,200
What?

389
00:20:09,900 --> 00:20:10,900
What?

390
00:20:11,233 --> 00:20:15,100
You want me to collaborate
with a web novel writer?

391
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:16,733
Wait.

392
00:20:17,877 --> 00:20:19,533
Hold on a second.

393
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:24,233
You want a contract?

394
00:20:24,928 --> 00:20:27,200
Turn my novel into a webtoon?

395
00:20:28,733 --> 00:20:32,433
Okay. You'll match me
with a webtoon artist?

396
00:20:33,400 --> 00:20:34,633
The contract terms...

397
00:20:36,300 --> 00:20:37,700
Wrong number.

398
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,100
- What is it?
- Hey, Mom.

399
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:41,900
What was that call?

400
00:20:41,900 --> 00:20:43,500
What? Nothing.

401
00:20:43,700 --> 00:20:45,848
Something about a card application.

402
00:20:46,133 --> 00:20:47,643
That's all voice phishing.

403
00:20:47,643 --> 00:20:49,645
Be careful, or you'll be in big trouble.

404
00:20:50,033 --> 00:20:52,133
I know. Anyway, what is it?

405
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,500
Can you call your brother?

406
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,400
He had his final interview yesterday...

407
00:20:57,700 --> 00:21:00,776
at a university recommended
by his professor.

408
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:04,461
I'm dying to know the result,

409
00:21:04,811 --> 00:21:06,300
but I feel awkward asking.

410
00:21:06,835 --> 00:21:09,733
Just wait. This is becoming an obsession.

411
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:11,533
Why are you so fixated on your kids?

412
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:14,045
Dr. Cho, that's harsh.

413
00:21:14,045 --> 00:21:16,200
Worrying about your kids isn't a disease.

414
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:18,600
We're all adults now.

415
00:21:19,100 --> 00:21:21,500
Do you think things will go your way...

416
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,800
just because you worry?

417
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:25,600
Now that you're grown,

418
00:21:26,033 --> 00:21:27,619
you think you raised yourselves?

419
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,853
Have kids of your own someday.

420
00:21:31,853 --> 00:21:33,784
Then you'll understand.

421
00:21:34,633 --> 00:21:36,700
That's why I don't want to get married.

422
00:21:37,400 --> 00:21:39,000
Life is already hard enough alone.

423
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,700
Are you against marriage?

424
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:43,824
Dr. Cho.

425
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:45,633
I didn't mean it like that.

426
00:21:46,900 --> 00:21:49,633
Please leave. I need to study.

427
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:52,600
Look at you acting all high and mighty.

428
00:21:53,333 --> 00:21:55,600
Fine, keep studying.

429
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:04,133
How will I get over this?

430
00:22:04,833 --> 00:22:06,833
My future looks bleak too.

431
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:14,400
Hello, I'm sorry about earlier.

432
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,133
About the contract details...

433
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,893
Meet in person? Yes.

434
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:22,633
Did we make any progress?

435
00:22:22,900 --> 00:22:26,300
Yes, we're tracking down...

436
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:28,700
the restaurant owner
who disappeared with the child.

437
00:22:29,003 --> 00:22:31,600
We're re-investigating
orphanages nationwide,

438
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:34,833
including overseas adoption records.

439
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:39,533
And I'd like to re-register Madam's DNA.

440
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:41,100
What do you mean?

441
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:44,800
We already registered it 20 years ago.

442
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:47,100
If we update it in the latest system,

443
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:50,733
the search algorithm
and database matching rate...

444
00:22:50,733 --> 00:22:52,233
will increase accordingly.

445
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:58,900
But we can't do that without telling her.

446
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,500
She'll find out anyway.

447
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:04,400
Why not be honest?

448
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:07,333
Her hopes have already been shattered
so many times.

449
00:23:08,533 --> 00:23:12,000
I can't bear to see...

450
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:14,733
her heart break again.

451
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:16,633
Then...

452
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,933
How about suggesting a health checkup?

453
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:25,955
Why is this house so well soundproofed?

454
00:23:28,900 --> 00:23:29,933
What are you doing there?

455
00:23:30,091 --> 00:23:31,829
Mother.

456
00:23:31,829 --> 00:23:33,400
I'm stretching. It feels great.

457
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:35,500
Good grief.

458
00:23:36,500 --> 00:23:37,900
Let me carry that for you.

459
00:23:37,900 --> 00:23:39,085
It's heavy. Give it to me.

460
00:23:39,085 --> 00:23:40,200
No, it's fine.

461
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,733
I'm dying to know
what those two are whispering about.

462
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,100
Should I cut some fruit and come in too?

463
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:02,400
Why is this so hard?

464
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:13,100
Why are you coming out already?

465
00:24:13,700 --> 00:24:15,233
They're done talking.

466
00:24:15,700 --> 00:24:19,200
Still, have some fruit
and talk a bit more.

467
00:24:21,033 --> 00:24:22,833
I'll be going now.

468
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:24,400
All right, good work.

469
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,435
Shall we go out for a walk
around the neighborhood?

470
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:30,800
Sure.

471
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:36,400
You worked hard.
We'll come back later and eat it.

472
00:24:45,033 --> 00:24:48,100
What do you mean you need me by your side?

473
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:50,900
My father's been told
he has at most a year,

474
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,533
maybe as little as six months.

475
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:58,400
In the end,
I'll be the one carrying Kangsu Group,

476
00:24:59,033 --> 00:25:01,333
so who else can I trust...

477
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:03,300
and rely on but you?

478
00:25:03,900 --> 00:25:05,100
I appreciate it,

479
00:25:05,700 --> 00:25:08,368
but I'm a cleaning contractor.
Did you forget?

480
00:25:08,368 --> 00:25:11,800
If you're willing,
I'll find a position for you.

481
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:13,933
It's not that simple.

482
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:16,900
I may have been an executive before,

483
00:25:16,900 --> 00:25:19,747
but I know nothing about this industry.

484
00:25:19,747 --> 00:25:22,520
Executives do similar work anywhere.

485
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,833
If you're by my side,

486
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:28,509
I'd feel like I have an army behind me.

487
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:31,600
Don't make emotional decisions.
Think it through.

488
00:25:32,233 --> 00:25:34,500
Let's pretend
we never had this conversation.

489
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:38,833
Did Gwon Sik tell you
not to stay by my side?

490
00:25:40,533 --> 00:25:43,000
What? Why would he?

491
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:46,125
I just can't figure that guy out.

492
00:25:46,300 --> 00:25:48,856
You've seen
how he always pushes back at me.

493
00:25:49,500 --> 00:25:52,333
If you're asking me this
to keep him in check,

494
00:25:54,300 --> 00:25:56,533
don't. I'm leaving.

495
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:05,400
Why does he always talk in circles?

496
00:26:05,833 --> 00:26:08,900
So is he going to stay by my side or not?

497
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:12,633
That kind of rent is possible
in this area.

498
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:15,400
That's true,
but the transportation is a bit...

499
00:26:16,033 --> 00:26:17,900
Then I'll look around a bit more.

500
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,500
- Yes, take your time.
- Yes.

501
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:21,232
Call me if you change your mind.

502
00:26:21,232 --> 00:26:22,256
- All right.
- Take care.

503
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:29,533
What brings you here?
You didn't even call first.

504
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,000
Are you on your way to work?

505
00:26:32,233 --> 00:26:34,533
Yes, I have an evening flight today.

506
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:36,885
You must be busy getting to work.

507
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,800
Did you get the interview results?

508
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:44,200
Yes, that's why I came.

509
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,200
What happened? Did it not go well?

510
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,200
No,

511
00:26:47,533 --> 00:26:51,100
he was accepted on the day
of the interview.

512
00:26:51,333 --> 00:26:54,741
My goodness,
why didn't you tell me sooner?

513
00:26:54,741 --> 00:26:56,100
I was so worried.

514
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:58,300
That's wonderful. Eun Hyeong did it.

515
00:26:59,833 --> 00:27:01,500
But, Mother...

516
00:27:02,300 --> 00:27:03,300
Yes?

517
00:27:04,633 --> 00:27:05,800
What should I do?

518
00:27:07,333 --> 00:27:09,600
What's wrong? What happened?

519
00:27:18,900 --> 00:27:20,933
The will must be somewhere.

520
00:27:22,100 --> 00:27:23,200
What is this?

521
00:27:39,700 --> 00:27:42,160
Why was this cheap necklace...

522
00:27:42,833 --> 00:27:46,200
wrapped up so carefully?

523
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,000
Su Jeong!

524
00:27:50,733 --> 00:27:51,733
Mother.

525
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:07,900
(Our Happy Days)

526
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,800
She hid it quickly when Father came in.

527
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,205
There must be some big secret
he doesn't know about.

528
00:28:14,633 --> 00:28:17,000
Are you crazy? You're going to tell
the foundation you're turning it down?

529
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,600
Did you tell Mother about the money?

530
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,500
Why don't you realize
this is your last chance?

531
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:23,100
Is this Joy? Can I take a look?

532
00:28:23,100 --> 00:28:24,133
I have a meeting now.

533
00:28:24,133 --> 00:28:25,400
I can't take this anymore.

534
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,500
How dare they mess with my Joy?

535
00:28:28,133 --> 00:28:29,400
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
